2026-02-27 | Move All Zeros to End

	Question
Given arr[],
move all zeros to the right end
while preserving the order of non-zero elements.

	Approach
1.	Use two-pointer technique.
2.	Maintain:
		insertPos â†’ index where next non-zero should go.
3.	Traverse the array:
		If arr[i] != 0:
			Swap arr[i] with arr[insertPos]
			Increment insertPos.
4.	This ensures:
		-	All non-zero elements shift forward.
		-	Zeros automatically move to the end.
5.	Time Complexity:
		O(n)
6.	Space Complexity:
		O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    void moveZeroes(vector<int>& arr) {
        int insertPos = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < arr.size(); i++) {
            if (arr[i] != 0) {
                swap(arr[i], arr[insertPos]);
                insertPos++;
            }
        }
    }
};

	Key Insight
By compacting non-zero elements to the front
using a single pass,
zeros naturally shift to the end.
This achieves an optimal O(n) in-place solution.
